  "text": "In practice, average SNR of the SNs is different due to differences in distances to the CN. In this case, giving priority to the SNs with the good channel conditions causes unfairness in WSN. Instead of giving priority to the SNs that have SNR over the threshold, an alternative CSI metric can be considered that is normalized SNR (NSNR). Therefore, the resource allocation may be provided 8 International Journal of Distributed Sensor Networks more efficiently. The PDF and CDF expressions of NSNR metric are given by [CITATION_1] ",
